Southwest China's Chengdu City, capital of Sichuan Province, is regarded as China's second-best flower city in the minds of many gardeners, after Kunming only. Tao Yuan, CGTN reporter, visited one garden in the city. The owner shared her views on taking care of flowers. Check out the video to learn more! About 'Chinese New Year Flowers': To celebrate the Chinese New Year, Chinese people buy a variety of flowers. These flowers can not only decorate their homes but also represent good wishes. What kind of flowers did they buy across China? What do these plants symbolize? Explore more in our new series "Chinese New Year Flowers"! For more: Chinese New Year Flowers: Into Beijing 'Chinese New Year Flowers': Foreigner bought flowers to welcome Spring Festival in Shanghai Chinese New Year Flowers: Let's go to the flower market in Xinjiang Chinese New Year flowers: Onward! Hainan Chinese New Year Flowers: Flower boat fair revives age-old tradition in Guangdong Chinese New Year Flowers: Kunming Dounan flower market (Cover image designed by CGTN's Li Wenyi) (If you want to contribute and have specific expertise, please contact us at nature@cgtn.com.)